-------------------------Message 1 ---------------------------------- 
Date: Thu, 17 Jan 2008 13:17:47
From: Daniela Müller [daniela-mueller@gmx.de]
Subject: 5en Obrador de Lingüistica Occitana
E-mail this message to a friend:
http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=19-205.html&submissionid=166563&topicid=3&msgnumber=1  

Full Title: 5en Obrador de Lingüistica Occitana 
Short Title: OLO5 

Date: 04-Jul-2008 - 04-Jul-2008
Location: Tolosa/Toulouse, France 
Contact Person: Gerard Joan Barceló
Meeting Email: director@revistadoc.org
Web Site: http://www.revistadoc.org 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Subject Language(s): Gascon (gsc)
                     Auvergnat (auv)
                     Limousin (lms)
                     Languedocien (lnc)

Call Deadline: 01-Apr-2008 

Meeting Description

The 5th Workshop on Occitan Linguistics will take place in Tolosa on July 4th
2008 in the CROM building (Centre de Ressources Occitanes et Méridionales, 56
carrièra del Taur / rue du Taur, 31000 Tolosa/Toulouse). 

Call for Papers

The workshop is organized by the Association for Occitan Linguistics and invites
contributions from all fields of synchronic or diachronic Occitan linguistics
(lexicology, syntax, morphology, phonology, dialectology, etc.). Comparative
approaches are also welcomed. Contributions can focus on results from completed
as well as ongoing research. All abstracts submitted should represent original
and unpublished work.

Abstracts are invited for 20 minutes talks, followed by 10 minutes discussion.

The workshop languages are Occitan, another Romance language or English.

Interested parties should send the title of their proposed talk accompanied by
an abstract (Word document) by e-mail to articles@revistadoc.org in two
versions, one anonymous and one with your name and affiliation, before April 1st
2008. Papers may be published in the online journal ''Lingüistica Occitana''
(www.revistadoc.org), if approved by the journal's scientific committee.

There will be no conference fee.

Scientific Committee: 
Miriam Bras, Jacques Bres, Aitor Carrera, Arvèi Lieutard, Patric Sauzet and
Domergue Sumien (members of the scientific committee of the journal)

Workshop Organizers: 
Gerard Joan Barceló, Daniela Müller and Patric Sauzet

Important Dates:
Deadline for abstract submissions: April 1st 2008
Notification of acceptance: May 1st 2008
Workshop: July 4th 2008

La cinquena edicion de l'Obrador de Linguistica Occitana se debanarà a Tolosa lo
4 de julh de 2008, al CROM, 56 carrièra del Taur.

Organizat per l'associacion ''Linguistica occitana'', l'Obrador es dubèrt a
totes los que vòlon intervenir sus una question de linguistica occitana (lexic,
sintaxi, morfologia, fonologia, dialectologia, ...) tant en sincronia coma en
diacronia. Cap de tèma i es pas impausat. Los apròchis comparatius son
possibles. Aquel encontre pòt èsser l'escasença de presentar un trabalh acabat o
en cors d'elaboracion.

Las lengas de comunicacion seràn l'occitan, una autra lenga romanica o l'anglés.

La participacion al collòqui se  fa a res-non-còst.

Se prevei un temps de 30 minutas per cada comunicacion (20 +10 minutas de
discussion).
 
Las personas interessadas devon mandar per corrièr electronic a
articles@revistadoc.org una proposicion de comunicacion acompanhada d'un resumit
(de 10 a 30 linhas, format Word) en dos exemplars, un de dos anonim, abans lo 1r
d'abril de 2008. Seràn assabentadas de l'acceptacion ou del refús abans lo 1r de
mai de 2008. Possibilitat de publicacion -après consultacion del comitat de
lectura- dins la revista electronica Linguistica Occitana, que son sit es a
l'adreiça http://www.revistadoc.org
 
Comitat Scientific: 
Miriam Bras, Jacques Bres, Aitor Carrera, Arvèi Lieutard, Patric Sauzet e
Domergue Sumien (sòcis del comitat de lectura de la revista).
Comitat d'organizacion: Gerard Joan Barceló, Daniela Müller e Patric Sauzet



	
